 is an engaging and unique study, showing that policy advocacy, both foreign and domestic, is best understood as a site where Muslim American identity is performed and negotiated.Claiming Belonging offers ever-timely insight into the place of Muslims in American political life and, in the process, sheds light on one of the fastest growing and most internally dynamic American minority groups.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aIslam and politicszUnited States. 0aIslam and statezUnited States. 0aIslamophobiazUnited States. 0aMuslimsxPolitical activityzUnited States. 0aMuslimszUnited StatesxSocial conditionsy21st century. 4aIslamic Religion & Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh  aMuslim American advocacy, Islamophobia and Anti-Muslim discrimination, Minority group politics in the United States, The Council on American-Islamic Relations, Muslim American identity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150175361940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501753619423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501753619/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE